headlines.description: — Miami Heat coach Erik Spoelstra thought his players turned back the clock Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler's late flurry helps Heat put away Pacers 87-82

headlines.description: — The Brooklyn Nets are rolling, and Kyrie Irving is only talking about their commitment to playing hard and stacking up wins.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant, Irving lead well-rested Nets past Wizards 112-100

headlines.description: — Tyus Jones had 22 points and 11 assists, Dillon Brooks added 18 points and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Atlanta Hawks 128-103 on Monday night in a game in which both teams were without key starters.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jones, Brooks power Memphis to 128-103 win over Atlanta

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 38 points and 11 rebounds in his return from a one-game absence, and Spencer Dinwiddie added 20 points and 10 assists as the Dallas Mavericks beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 121-114 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 38, Dinwiddie 20 as Mavs beat Thunder 121-114

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Spurs coach Gregg Popovich screamed on the sidelines, pounded the scorer’s table and then demonstrated the defensive stance he wanted his young players to show in the final seconds against Cleveland.
headlines.shortLinkText: Johnson, Spurs hold off Mitchell, Cavs to win 3rd in row

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard tied his own franchise record by making 11 3-pointers and finished with 38 points, leading the Portland Trail Blazers over the Minnesota Timberwolves 133-112 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard ties own Blazers mark with 11 3-pointers, beats Minn

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard came to the bench with a message for his Los Angeles Clippers teammates.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard, George lead Clippers over NBA-best Celtics, 113-93
